Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_proto_model(25.10)                                  set_proto_model(25.10)

Name
       set_proto_model  - The set_proto_model command specifies the model type
       of a specific module

Syntax
       set_proto_model

       [-help]

       -model <name_list>

       [-type {full | flex_module | flex_instgroup}]

       [-create_total_area <number> | -create_gate_area <number> |

       {-create_gate_count <number> -create_area_per_gate <number>}]

       [-create_extra_macro {macro_name <number>

       [macro_name <number>] ...}

       [-planDesign_target_util number]

       [-reset]

       The set_proto_model command specifies the model type of a specific mod-
       ule.

       Note: Wildcards are not supported by this command.

Parameters
       -create_area_per_gate number
              Specifies the area per gate.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -create_extra_macro

              {macro_namenumber[macro_namenumber] ...}"  Specifies  the  addi-
              tional macro(s) of a module that you want to add in the original
              netlist.  If  you  wish to add extra macros, this option changes
              the netlist.

              For example, if your original netlist has macro A and you  spec-
              ify  an  additional macro named macro B, then the flexModel with
              have both macro A and macro B.

              Data_type: string, optional

               -create_gate_area <number>" Specifies the total area of  gates.
              This  value  does not include macro area. Its unit is square mi-
              crons. The total area (equivalent to -create_total_area) is cal-
              culated as the sum of specified total gate area and macro area.

              Data_type: float, optional

               -create_gate_count <number>" Specifies the number of gates.  If
              you  specify  this  parameter, you also need to specify area per
              gate value.Total gate area is equal to the product of gate count
              and area per gate. The calculated total gate area does  not  in-
              clude  the  macro  area. So, the total area (equivalent to -cre-
              ate_total_area) is equal to the sum of total gate area  and  the
              macro area.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -create_total_area <number>
              Specifies  the module area of a model that includes the standard
              cell area and the macro area.

              Note: A warning message is issued when  macro  area  is  greater
              than the area specified using the -create_total_area parameter.

              Note:  For -create_area_per_gate number, -create_total_area num-
              ber, -create_gate_area number and -create_gate_count number; you
              can define the area instead of the value calculated by the  tool
              (for  times when you wish to specify  larger area for the module
              to achieve better results).

              Data_type: float, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_proto_model parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man set_proto_model.

       -model<name_list>
              Specifies a name for the model type.

              Data_type: string, required

       -planDesign_target_util <number>
              Specifies  the target utilization value to derive initial module
              size of a model. This value is used by the proto_design  command
              to derive the module size of a specified flexModel if its module
              is not placed yet.

              Default: current design utilization

              Note:  You  can  reduce the target utilization value by 10 to 20
              percent to account for 10 to 20  percent  increase  in  instance
              count during optimization.

               If the post-target utilization is 0.75, then Cadence recommends
              you to set the following:

              set_proto_mode -model <name_list> -planDesign_target_util 0.55

              Data_type: float, optional

       -reset Resets all the attributes of a module.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type {full | flex_module | flex_instgroup}
              Specifies the model type as full or a flex module or a flexInst-
              group.  You  use  this  parameter  when  you  want  to convert a
              flex_module back to the original netlist or converse.

              Data_type: enum, optional

Examples
              * The following command specifies the number of gates  as  10000
                and area per gate as 0.65 for the tdsp_core model:

                set_proto_model   -model  tdsp_core  -create_gate_count  10000
                -create_area_per_gate 0.65 -type flex_module

              * The following command specifies model alu as flex_module  with
                total area 1000 and target utilization 0.75:

                set_proto_model  -model  alu  -type  flex_module   -create_to-
                tal_area   1000 -planDesign_target_util 0.75

              * The following command specifies model crossbar as  flex_module
                with total area 3000:

                set_proto_model -model crossbar  -type flex_module -create_to-
                tal_area   3000

              * The  following  command  specifies  the  extra macro {pllclk 2
                ram128x164} of the chico model:

                set_proto_model -model  chico  -create_extra_macro  {pllclk  2
                ram128x164}

              * The  following  command  resets  all the attributes of the alu
                model:

                set_proto_model -model alu -reset

